    "In this section, we explain the open-set recognition problem in two application areas: Open set recognition in computer vision: In real-world recognition problems, it is inevitable to introduce unknown points, events, or observations in a collected dataset.",
    "Human error, low-precision machine operation, or the natural environment usually cause those unknowns (vibration, geomagnetic activity, illumination, etc.)",
